OL,3,CTrapped researchers in Antarctica call
OL,4,Cfor help after 'assault' of colleague
OL,6,FIt said: "Regrettably, (his) behaviour
OL,7,Fhas escalated to a point that is
OL,8,Fdeeply disturbing. Specifically, he
OL,9,Fphysically assaulted (name withheld),
OL,10,Fwhich is a grave violation of personal
OL,11,Fsafety and workplace norms."
OL,13,F"Furthermore, he threatened to kill
OL,14,F(name withheld), creating an
OL,15,Fenvironment of fear and intimidation.
OL,16,FI remain deeply concerned about my own
OL,17,Fsafety, constantly wondering if I
OL,18,Fmight become the next victim."
