OL,3,CTrapped researchers in Antarctica call
OL,4,Cfor help after 'assault' of colleague
OL,6,FThe Times reported that George said:
OL,7,F"There was a verbal altercation
OL,8,Fbetween the team leader and this
OL,9,Fperson. Then it escalated and then
OL,10,Fthat person did physically assault the
OL,11,Fleader.
OL,13,F"You can imagine what it's like, it is
OL,14,Fclose quarters and people do get cabin
OL,15,Ffever. It can be very disorientating."
OL,17,FBecause of the conditions at the base,
OL,18,FGeorge said that researchers undergo
OL,19,Fpsychometric assessments before
OL,20,Fdeployment.
